DIAPENSIACEAE
PLANTS OF Alabama
THE MORTON ARBORETUM, LISLE, IL. 60532
Col. No. 5790 Clay Co.
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt

W. side of Talladega Mts., Talladega Nat'l
Forest, Cheaha St. Park, 27 mi S of Oxford
Upland forest of Pine-oak-hickory & under-
story of *Rhododendron*, *Kalmia* & *Viburnum*.
Locally common in damp woods & at edges,
rhizomatous, 5 white petals, 5 fertile &
5 sterile stamens, superior ovary.
W. Hess May 14, 1983
